Rob Griffin

Data scientist with a strong background in experimental research, statistics and programming. A career in Evolutionary Quantitative Genetics seeded an interest in data science and provided me with considerable experience using R for complex statistical analysis and data visualisation. In 2020, I decided to pursue a career in data science and joined a graduate program at AstraZeneca as a Statistical Programmer, being promoted from the program one year early. I am now looking to make the next step and find a role with an emphasis on research, analysis and interpretation in data-oriented projects, where my tendency to show initiative and strengths in critical thinking and creative problem solving can be of greater value.
